events.description: King Henry III of England marries Eleanor of Provence.
events.html: • 1236 – King Henry III of England marries Eleanor of Provence.[1]

events.description: Andrew III of Hungary dies, ending the Árpád dynasty in Hungary.
events.html: • 1301 – Andrew III of Hungary dies, ending the Árpád dynasty in Hungary.[2]

events.description: The Third Battle of Panipat is fought in India between the Afghans under Ahmad Shah Durrani and the Marathas.
events.html: • 1761 – The Third Battle of Panipat is fought in India between the Afghans under Ahmad Shah Durrani and the Marathas.[3]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: Ratification Day, United States - Congress ratifies the Treaty of Paris with Great Britain.
events.html: • 1784 – American Revolutionary War: Ratification Day, United States - Congress ratifies the Treaty of Paris with Great Britain.[4]

events.description: The Battle of Rivoli is fought with a decisive French victory by Napoleon Bonaparte, marking the beginning of the end of the War of the First Coalition and the start of French hegemony over Italy for two decades.
events.html: • 1797 – The Battle of Rivoli is fought with a decisive French victory by Napoleon Bonaparte, marking the beginning of the end of the War of the First Coalition and the start of French hegemony over Italy for two decades.[5]

events.description: Treaty of Kiel: Frederick VI of Denmark cedes the Kingdom of Norway to Charles XIII of Sweden in return for Pomerania.
events.html: • 1814 – Treaty of Kiel: Frederick VI of Denmark cedes the Kingdom of Norway to Charles XIII of Sweden in return for Pomerania.[6]

events.description: Napoleon III of France escapes an assassination attempt made by Felice Orsini and his accomplices in Paris.
events.html: • 1858 – Napoleon III of France escapes an assassination attempt made by Felice Orsini and his accomplices in Paris.[7]

events.description: RMS Oceanic, the largest ship afloat since SS Great Eastern, is launched.
events.html: • 1899 – RMS Oceanic, the largest ship afloat since SS Great Eastern, is launched.[8][9]

events.description: Giacomo Puccini's Tosca opens in Rome.
events.html: • 1900 – Giacomo Puccini's Tosca opens in Rome.[10]

events.description: An earthquake in Kingston, Jamaica kills more than 1,000 people.
events.html: • 1907 – An earthquake in Kingston, Jamaica kills more than 1,000 people.[11]

events.description: Roald Amundsen's South Pole expedition makes landfall on the eastern edge of the Ross Ice Shelf.
events.html: • 1911 – Roald Amundsen's South Pole expedition makes landfall on the eastern edge of the Ross Ice Shelf.[12]

events.description: Norway claims Queen Maud Land in Antarctica.
events.html: • 1939 – Norway claims Queen Maud Land in Antarctica.[13]

events.description: World War II: Japan begins Operation Ke, the successful operation to evacuate its forces from Guadalcanal during the Guadalcanal Campaign.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Japan begins Operation Ke, the successful operation to evacuate its forces from Guadalcanal during the Guadalcanal Campaign.[14]

events.description: World War II: Franklin D. Roosevelt and Winston Churchill begin the Casablanca Conference to discuss strategy and study the next phase of the war.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Franklin D. Roosevelt and Winston Churchill begin the Casablanca Conference to discuss strategy and study the next phase of the war.[15]

events.description: National Airlines Flight 83 crashes during landing at Philadelphia International Airport, killing seven passengers and crew.
events.html: • 1951 – National Airlines Flight 83 crashes during landing at Philadelphia International Airport, killing seven passengers and crew.[16]

events.description: NBC's long-running morning news program Today debuts, with host Dave Garroway.
events.html: • 1952 – NBC's long-running morning news program Today debuts, with host Dave Garroway.[17]

events.description: Josip Broz Tito is elected the first President of Yugoslavia.
events.html: • 1953 – Josip Broz Tito is elected the first President of Yugoslavia.[18]

entities.name: List of heads of state of Yugoslavia

events.description: The Hudson Motor Car Company merges with Nash-Kelvinator Corporation forming the American Motors Corporation.
events.html: • 1954 – The Hudson Motor Car Company merges with Nash-Kelvinator Corporation forming the American Motors Corporation.[19]

events.description: Kripalu Maharaj is named fifth Jagadguru (world teacher) after giving seven days of speeches before 500 Hindu scholars.
events.html: • 1957 – Kripalu Maharaj is named fifth Jagadguru (world teacher) after giving seven days of speeches before 500 Hindu scholars.[20]

events.description: The Reserve Bank of Australia, the country's central bank and banknote issuing authority authorized by the 1959 Reserve Bank Act, is established.
events.html: • 1960 – The Reserve Bank of Australia, the country's central bank and banknote issuing authority authorized by the 1959 Reserve Bank Act, is established.[21]

events.description: Counterculture of the 1960s: The Human Be-In takes place in San Francisco, California's Golden Gate Park, launching the Summer of Love.
events.html: • 1967 – Counterculture of the 1960s: The Human Be-In takes place in San Francisco, California's Golden Gate Park, launching the Summer of Love.[22]

events.description: USS Enterprise fire: An accidental explosion aboard the USS Enterprise near Hawaii kills 28 people.
events.html: • 1969 – USS Enterprise fire: An accidental explosion aboard the USS Enterprise near Hawaii kills 28 people.[23]

events.description: Queen Margrethe II of Denmark ascends the throne, the first Queen of Denmark since 1412 and the first Danish monarch not named Frederik or Christian since 1513.
events.html: • 1972 – Queen Margrethe II of Denmark ascends the throne, the first Queen of Denmark since 1412 and the first Danish monarch not named Frederik or Christian since 1513.

events.description: Elvis Presley's concert Aloha from Hawaii is broadcast live via satellite, and sets the record as the most watched broadcast by an individual entertainer in television history.
events.html: • 1973 – Elvis Presley's concert Aloha from Hawaii is broadcast live via satellite, and sets the record as the most watched broadcast by an individual entertainer in television history.

entities.name: List of most watched television broadcasts

events.description: Sinking of the MS Jan Heweliusz: In Poland's worst peacetime maritime disaster, ferry MS Jan Heweliusz sinks off the coast of Rügen, drowning 55 passengers and crew; nine crew-members are saved.
events.html: • 1993 – Sinking of the MS Jan Heweliusz: In Poland's worst peacetime maritime disaster, ferry MS Jan Heweliusz sinks off the coast of Rügen, drowning 55 passengers and crew; nine crew-members are saved.

entities.name: Sinking of the MS Jan Heweliusz

events.description: The national flag of the Republic of Georgia, the so-called "five cross flag", is restored to official use after a hiatus of some 500 years.
events.html: • 2004 – The national flag of the Republic of Georgia, the so-called "five cross flag", is restored to official use after a hiatus of some 500 years.

events.description: Yemen declares an open war against the terrorist group al-Qaeda.
events.html: • 2010 – Yemen declares an open war against the terrorist group al-Qaeda.

events.description: President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali of Tunisia seeks refuge in Saudi Arabia after a series of demonstrations against his regime, considered to be the birth of the Arab Spring.
events.html: • 2011 – President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali of Tunisia seeks refuge in Saudi Arabia after a series of demonstrations against his regime, considered to be the birth of the Arab Spring.

events.description: Multiple explosions reported near the Sarinah Building, Jakarta, followed by shootout between perpetrators and the police, killing seven people. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant claimed responsibility.
events.html: • 2016 – Multiple explosions reported near the Sarinah Building, Jakarta, followed by shootout between perpetrators and the police, killing seven people. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant claimed responsibility.[24]
